text: {'data': 'A person who has suffered severe irritation of the eyes or respiratory organs as the result of exposure to the product should avoid all contact with isocyanates for 2 - 3 months to prevent sensitization. A medical check - up should be carried out 3 - 6 weeks after restarting work with the product. Spilled product should be covered with a moist liquidbinding material, e.g. a chemical binder based on hydrated calcium silicate ( Hybilat ) . Sand or sawdust can be used in an emergency although the fire risk associated with sawdust should be borne in mind. The binder should subsequently be transferred to a waste container and stored under moist conditions in a secure outdoor location. The container should not be closed. The binder should be disposed of by incineration at a suitable incineration plant. Any residue of the product in empty containers can be made harmless using a special neutralizing solution. The cure time and temperature required are also dependent upon the choice of coreactant. Combining Desmodur BL 3175 A with hydroxyl - functional polyesters such as Desmophen 670 A 80 gives coatings with high flexibility and hardness. text: {'data': 'Packing and transport: ONGRONAT® XP 1101 can be loaded and transported in tank road tankers, 1000 | containers, 225 kg non - returnable metal drums, or in metal cans under nitrogen blanket. The loading temperature of ONGRONAT® XP 1101 is 40 - 50 ℃ in bulk and 20 - 30 ℃ in the case of drummed product or in intermediate bulk containers ( IBCs ) . Please note that based on the distance of the destination the delivery temperature may differ from the loading temperature, but still remains in the range of 20 - 40 ℃ in the case of bulk product. When transporting ONGRONAT® XP 1101 in drums or IBCs the temperature must be kept in the range of 20 - 30 ℃, therefore cold shocks and prolonged exposure of the containers ( drums or IBCs ) to intensive sunlight must be avoided. ONGRONAT® XP 1101 is shipped according to the above mentioned delivery temperature ranges in the lack of any special requirement. Storage: It is recommended to store ONGRONAT® XP 1101 at room temperature [ 20 - 30 ℃ ) . Under these conditions the shelf life of the ONGRONAT® XP 1101 is six ( 6 ) months from the date of production. The material must be kept dry at all times. It must be protected from water ingress and atmospheric moisture. In order to protect the material from the latter, a dry inert gas blanket ( nitrogen ) with a dew point of - 40 ℃ must be applied to the containers ( drums or storage tanks ) . Dry air is not recommended for this purpose as it may cause oxidation of the product and therefore can result in the change ( yellowing ) of its colour. text: {'data': 'ONGRONAT @ CO 4050 can be packed and transported in road tankers, 1000 | containers ( IBCs ) , 225 kg non - returnable metal drums, or in metal cans under nitrogen blanket. The loading temperature is 40 - 45 ℃. Please note that based on the distance of the destination the delivery temperature may differ from the loading temperature, but still remains in the range of 20 - 45 ℃ delivering the product in bulk. In case of shipping by normal truck ( in drums or IBCs ) the delivery temperature can not be warranted. text: {'data': 'Aquolin® 278 is a water dispersible polyisocyanate based on hexamethylene diisocyanate ( HDI ) . In combination with waterborne polyurethane, polyacrylate, etc., it can be used for water - borne coatings. Thanks to its low viscosity and ease of hand - mixing, Aquolin® 278 can be used to prepare “solvent - free hardener” in order to produce ultralow VOC coatings. After addition of Aquolin® 278, the ready - to - use mixture must be used within the pot life.', 'label': [[60, 94, 'qualitative_value']]}
label: Base monomer

text: {'data': 'To accelerate the drying and ensure adequate perfor - mance properties of systems containing DesmodurN 3300 A, it is advisable to add 0.005 - 0.01 % dibutyltin dilaurate based on total resin solids. Othe rcatalysts which can be used effectively are Desmorapid PP ( up to 0.5 % ) or, 8 % zinc octoate ( up to 0.2 % ) ,each based on the total resin solids of the system. Adding catalysts affects the pot life of the coating material and should be evaluated prior to use. High solids coatings generally show a slower cure response than lower solids systems. In many cases, forced drying is advisable to maintain production rates.', 'label': []}

text: {'data': 'Bayhydur 302 water - dispersible polyisocyanate is a solvent - free, water - dispersible crosslinking agent for two - component waterborne polyurethane coatings. Suitable coreactants are the hydroxyl - functional waterborne resins such as Bayhydrol® VP LS 2235. Bayhydur 302 is dispersed in the aqueous resin by direct addition and under agitation just prior to use. Reaction occurs under ambient conditions. The potlife varies depending on the coreactant and NCO:OH ratio. Coatings formulated with Bayhydur 302 water - dispersible polyisocyanate have good gloss and chemical resistance. These coatings have good flexibility while maintaining film hardness. Bayhydur 302 water - dispersible polyisocyanate is suitable for industrial finishing, special purpose substrates, and wood furniture. Bayhydur 302 water - dispersible polyisocyanate can also be used as an additive with waterborne dispersions to improve film properties. As with any product, use of Bayhydur 302 in a given application must be tested ( including but not limited to field testing ) in advance by the user to determine suitability.', 'label': []}
